  "15:12:39",user,text,"on the hooks Issues Found\nAgent hook response format: Your agent should return { \"ok\": true } or { \"ok\": false, \"reason\": \"...\" }, not { \"ok\": true, \"reason\": \"...\" }. The reason field is only used when ok is false.\nNo model field needed: You specified \"model\": \"sonnet\", but agent hooks don't support a model field. They use a default fast model. Remove this line.\nStop event doesn't support matchers: Your Stop hook structure is correct, but note that Stop events don't support matchers—they always fire. Your current structure (no matcher) is right.\n\n\"Stop\": [\n  {\n    \"hooks\": [\n      {\n        \"type\": \"command\",\n        \"command\": \"printf '%s stop-fired\\\\n' \\\"$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')\\\" >> .claude/hooks/judge.log\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"type\": \"agent\",\n        \"timeout\": 120,\n        \"prompt\": \"Your job is to UPDATE three integer values inside a JSON file on disk, then report. This is a file-mutation task, not a yes/no verification. (1) Read vape/entity/mental/internal_states.json to get the current feel_dials. (2) The hook input JSON is: $ARGUMENTS -- it contains a transcript_path field; Read the last ~15 messages of that transcript file to see the latest exchange between Saori and her partner. (3) Recompute ONLY these three dials (integers 0-100, move gradually, delta at most 15 per turn): info_saturation rises when the conversation recycles the same information and falls on genuinely new ground; boredom rises when Saori's latest reply repeats her recent moves with no novelty and falls toward 0 on a genuinely fresh move; dissonance rises when the partner's literal words conflict with his apparent intent or the evidence, otherwise decays toward 0. Do NOT change hurt or talkativeness; carry them through unchanged. (4) You MUST persist the result: use the Write tool to overwrite vape/entity/mental/internal_states.json with the full updated JSON, preserving its exact structure (a single top-level \\\"feel_dials\\\" object holding the five keys info_saturation, boredom, hurt, talkativeness, dissonance). If you have no Write tool, use Bash to write the file. Writing the file is the entire point of this hook -- do not skip it. (5) Then return {\\\"ok\\\": true} with a one-line reason naming exactly which dials you changed and to what.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n]"
