  "16:30:58",assistant,text,"Current file is `32/8/0/70/0` (the background run wrote it at 16:28) — and one thing to flag in a second. But first, your question.\n\n## What `$ARGUMENTS` is for\n\nIt's a **placeholder** in a hook's `prompt` field. Before Claude Code sends the prompt to the model, it replaces `$ARGUMENTS` with the **hook input JSON** for that event. Straight from the docs: *\"Use `$ARGUMENTS` as a placeholder for the hook input JSON.\"*\n\nFor a **Stop** hook, that JSON carries the event's context — `session_id`, `transcript_path`, `cwd`, `stop_hook_active`, `hook_event_name`. And in practice it gives the model enough of the **recent conversation** to judge the turn — that's *why* the gate could write things like *\"Saori's last message discusses the mechanism… the background_tasks list shows only the voice server\"*. It was reading the turn through `$ARGUMENTS`.\n\nSo in our prompt — `\"…refresh Saori's feel dials from this turn: $ARGUMENTS\"` — the `$ARGUMENTS` is what lets the gate-model **see what just happened** so it can decide whether to bounce me.\n\n**Two honest caveats about it:**\n1. A prompt hook has **no tools**, so it can't open `transcript_path` itself — it only gets whatever the hook input already inlines. So `$ARGUMENTS` is the model's *whole* view of the turn.\n2. In the current wiring, `$ARGUMENTS` feeds the **gate**, not the judge. When I get bounced, I write *my own* one-line summary to `dial-judge` — so the raw `$ARGUMENTS` isn't what reaches the judge. If you'd want the actual transcript to flow all the way to the judge, that's a different wire.\n\n## The flag (relevant to this)\n\nThe judge just reported `info_saturation 40→32, boredom 12→8` — but the **actual prior** state was `32/5`, not `40/12`. So its reported baseline was wrong. Either it's misreporting, or it's **not anchoring on the current file values** (it seems to default to the original 40/12). That undermines \"move gradually *from current*.\" This is exactly the argument for your point-4 instinct, just flipped: rather than trust the subagent's Read, **pass the current dial values into the invocation** so it judges from ground truth. Want me to wire that?"
